Hi,<br><br>I have simple MPI program  that uses MPI_comm_spawn to create additional child processes. Using&nbsp;&nbsp;MPI_Intercomm_merge,&nbsp;I&nbsp;merge&nbsp;the&nbsp;child&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;parent&nbsp;communicator&nbsp;resulting&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;expanded&nbsp;user defined intracommunicator.&nbsp;I know MPI_COMM_WORLD is a constant which is statically initialized during MPI_Init call. But is&nbsp;there&nbsp;a&nbsp;way&nbsp;to&nbsp;update&nbsp;the&nbsp;value&nbsp;of&nbsp;MPI_COMM_WORLD&nbsp;at runtime to&nbsp;reflect&nbsp;this&nbsp;expanded&nbsp;set of processes?&nbsp;Is&nbsp;it&nbsp;possible&nbsp;to&nbsp;some how reinitialize&nbsp;MPI_COMM_WORLD&nbsp;using&nbsp;ompi_comm_init()&nbsp;function?
